📅 Week 3：Sprint 1
Mon, Mar 16
Held Sprint 1 Retrospective and Planning, confirmed team task assignments across all 6 Epics, and began development on US-01 (Register) and US-23 (Main Navigation layout); no blockers.

Tue, Mar 17
US-01 (Register) and US-02 (Login) completed with authentication logic; US-06 (Vocabulary list) and US-11 (Listening audio player) UI scaffolding started in parallel; no blockers.

Wed, Mar 18
US-03 (Logout), US-04 (Password Recovery), and US-05 (Concurrent Login Protection) implemented; US-07 (Word definition + example) and US-08 (Admin vocabulary) content integrated into Vocabulary module; no blockers.

Thu, Mar 19
US-09 (Vocabulary self-test), US-10 (Word mastery tracking), US-12 (Lecture recordings), US-13 (Listening comprehension questions), and US-14 (Answer explanations) all completed; began Speaking module development; no blockers.

Fri, Mar 20
US-15 (Speaking prompts), US-16 (Microphone recording), US-17 (Keyword scoring + feedback), and US-18 (Replay recordings) implemented; Epic 4 Speaking module fully functional; minor microphone permission issue on Android identified, to be resolved next week.

📅 Week 4 ：Sprint 2
Mon, Mar 23
Microphone permission issue resolved; US-19 (Support section layout), US-20 (Written guides), US-21 (Video tutorials), and US-22 (Topic categorisation) completed; Epic 5 Support section fully delivered; no blockers.

Tue, Mar 24
US-24 (Forum browse) and US-25 (Senior student posting) implemented; full cross-module integration testing conducted, UI inconsistencies fixed, and all 25 User Stories across 6 Epics confirmed as done; no blockers.
Meet the client for the first time.

Sprint 3 begins:
Thu, Mar 27
Kicked off Sprint 2 standup; US-51 (Virtual Pet growth logic) and US-53 (Pet-themed visual style) implementation started; plan to complete pet core system and begin skin-switching feature tomorrow; no blockers.

Fri, Mar 28
US-51 pet growth system completed and integrated with user activity data; US-52 (Pet skin unlock & switch) UI built with placeholder skins; US-53 theme applied globally across modules; plan to begin Epic 18 Wordle mini-game next week; no blockers.

📅 Week 5: Sprint 3
Mon, Mar 31
US-54 (Wordle game using vocabulary word list) core game logic implemented with letter feedback; US-55 (Earn coins from Wordle) logic drafted but reward calculation not yet connected to the global coin system; blocker: coin system architecture not finalised, causing integration conflicts between Wordle and Epic 19 — team agreed to define a unified reward interface before proceeding.

Tue, Apr 1
Coin system interface agreed upon and documented; US-56 (Cross-activity coin earning) and US-58 (Clear coin-earning rules per module) implemented and connected to Vocabulary, Listening, Speaking, and Forum modules; US-55 now unblocked and coin reward for Wordle integrated; no blockers.

Wed, Apr 2
US-57 (Speed-based coin reward for Listening) implemented with timer logic; Epic 19 Coins & Rewards system fully completed and tested; US-59 (Create/join study group) and US-61 (Group daily/weekly tasks) development started; blocker: real-time group task progress sync causing performance issues on lower-end devices, under investigation.

Thu, Apr 3
Performance issue partially mitigated by switching to polling instead of real-time sync; US-59 and US-61 completed; US-62 (Personal leaderboard) and US-65 (Calendar study planning) implemented; US-60 (Recruit group members via forum) deprioritised and moved back to Backlog due to time constraints; no further blockers.

Fri, Apr 4
US-66 (Mark calendar tasks + earn rewards) and US-67 (Group chat) completed; US-63 (Group leaderboard) and US-64 (Wordle leaderboard) scoped but moved to Backlog as remaining sprint time insufficient for proper testing; began initial code review pass on Epic 17–19; no blockers.

📅 Week 6: Sprint 4
Mon, Apr 7
US-68 (Private messaging between users) completed and tested; US-69 (Escape Room mini-game) development attempted but core task integration proved too complex within remaining sprint time — moved to Backlog; code review conducted on Epic 20 (Group System) and Epic 22 (Calendar); several minor logic issues identified and flagged for fixing.

Tue, Apr 8
Code review completed for Epic 21 (Leaderboard) and Epic 23 (Chat); bug fixes applied across group task sync, calendar reward trigger, and coin deduction edge cases; US-62 personal leaderboard refined based on review feedback; no blockers.

Wed, Apr 9
Final Sprint 2 standup — full code review pass completed across all delivered Epics (17–23); US-60, US-63, US-64, and US-69 confirmed as moved to Backlog; all remaining delivered User Stories verified as done and codebase prepared for Sprint 2 submission; no blockers.


